race.comment: Tricky. PROMISCUOUS GIRL (11) resumed further improved with a 58 win at the Sunshine Coast and then stepped up to a mile at Doomben beaten less than 2L. Uses the rail and will strip fitter again. Hard to peg back at each way odds. PHAROAH'S PROPHECY (5) brings strong form from Doomben where he's raced exclusively. He's free running and tackles the mile/track for the first time from a handy gate. Some trust is required but he's in a smart stable and can't be taken lightly. PUFF 'N' HARRY (9) won a Doomben Maiden off a 241-day break and then was in the market at Doomben but settled back and had too much to do. The step up to the mile should suit this fellow and he has a low gate today and the blinkers on for the first time. He has plenty of scope for improvement. LAVONI (10) is racing well and has placed 2/2 over a mile. Comes back in grade and can't be ruled out.
